CREATE TABLE `bigquery-public-data.ebi_chembl.compound_properties_30`
(
  molregno INT64 NOT NULL OPTIONS(description="Foreign key to compounds table (compound structure)"),
  mw_freebase FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="Molecular weight of parent compound"),
  alogp FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="Calculated ALogP"),
  hba INT64 OPTIONS(description="Number hydrogen bond acceptors"),
  hbd INT64 OPTIONS(description="Number hydrogen bond donors"),
  psa FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="Polar surface area"),
  rtb INT64 OPTIONS(description="Number rotatable bonds"),
  ro3_pass STRING OPTIONS(description=" Indicates whether the compound passes the rule-of-three (mw < 300, logP < 3 etc)"),

  cx_most_apka FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The most acidic pKa calculated using ChemAxon v17.29.0"),
  cx_most_bpka FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The most basic pKa calculated using ChemAxon v17.29.0"),
  cx_logp FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The calculated octanol/water partition coefficient using ChemAxon v17.29.0"),
  cx_logd FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The calculated octanol/water distribution coefficient at pH7.4 using ChemAxon v17.29.0"),
  molecular_species STRING OPTIONS(description="Indicates whether the compound is an acid/base/neutral"),
  full_mwt FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="Molecular weight of the full compound including any salts"),
  aromatic_rings INT64 OPTIONS(description="Number of aromatic rings"),
  heavy_atoms INT64 OPTIONS(description="Number of heavy (non-hydrogen) atoms"),
  qed_weighted FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="Weighted quantitative estimate of drug likeness (as defined by Bickerton et al., Nature Chem 2012)"),
  mw_monoisotopic FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="Monoisotopic parent molecular weight"),
  full_molformula STRING OPTIONS(description=" Molecular formula for the full compound (including any salt)"),
  hba_lipinski INT64 OPTIONS(description="Number of hydrogen bond acceptors calculated according to Lipinski's original rules (i.e., N + O count))"),
  hbd_lipinski INT64 OPTIONS(description="Number of hydrogen bond donors calculated according to Lipinski's original rules (i.e., NH + OH count)"),
  num_lipinski_ro5_violations INT64 OPTIONS(description="Number of violations of Lipinski's rule of five using HBA_LIPINSKI and HBD_LIPINSKI counts")

  oral INT64 NOT NULL OPTIONS(description="Indicates whether the drug is known to be administered orally."),
  parenteral INT64 NOT NULL OPTIONS(description="Indicates whether the drug is known to be administered parenterally"),
  topical INT64 NOT NULL OPTIONS(description="Indicates whether the drug is known to be administered topically."),
  black_box_warning INT64 NOT NULL OPTIONS(description="Indicates that the drug has a black box warning"),
  natural_product INT64 NOT NULL OPTIONS(description="Indicates whether the compound is natural product-derived (currently curated only for drugs)"),
  first_in_class INT64 NOT NULL OPTIONS(description="Indicates whether this is known to be the first compound of its class (e.g., acting on a particular target)."),
  chirality INT64 NOT NULL OPTIONS(description="Shows whether a drug is dosed as a racemic mixture (0), single stereoisomer (1) or is an achiral molecule (2)"),
  prodrug INT64 NOT NULL OPTIONS(description="Indicates that the molecule is a pro-drug (see molecule hierarchy for active component, where known)"),
  inorganic_flag INT64 NOT NULL OPTIONS(description="Indicates whether the molecule is inorganic (i.e., containing only metal atoms and <2 carbon atoms)"),
  usan_year INT64 OPTIONS(description="The year in which the application for a USAN/INN name was made"),
  availability_type INT64 OPTIONS(description="The availability type for the drug (0 = discontinued, 1 = prescription only, 2 = over the counter)"),
  usan_stem STRING OPTIONS(description="Where the compound has been assigned a USAN name, this indicates the stem, as described in the USAN_STEM table."),
  polymer_flag INT64 OPTIONS(description="Indicates whether a molecule is a small molecule polymer (e.g., polistyrex)"),
  usan_substem STRING OPTIONS(description="Where the compound has been assigned a USAN name, this indicates the substem"),
  usan_stem_definition STRING OPTIONS(description="Definition of the USAN stem"),
  indication_class STRING OPTIONS(description="Indication class(es) assigned to a drug in the USP dictionary"),
  withdrawn_flag INT64 NOT NULL OPTIONS(description="Flag indicating whether the drug has been withdrawn in at least one country (not necessarily in the US)"),
  withdrawn_year INT64 OPTIONS(description="Year the drug was first withdrawn in any country"),
  withdrawn_country STRING OPTIONS(description="List of countries/regions where the drug has been withdrawn"),
  withdrawn_reason STRING OPTIONS(description="Reasons for withdrawl (e.g., safety)"),
  withdrawn_class STRING OPTIONS(description=" High level categories for the withdrawn reason (e.g., Cardiotoxicity, Hepatotoxicity)")
